1
00:00:01,585 --> 00:00:02,836
-(CREAKING)
-(WHIMPERING)

2
00:00:04,463 --> 00:00:05,506
Run.

3
00:00:08,842 --> 00:00:10,302
I'm the Doctor, by the way.
What's your name?

4
00:00:10,427 --> 00:00:13,096
-Rose.
-Nice to meet you, Rose. Run for your life!

5
00:00:19,269 --> 00:00:20,854
It's gonna follow us!

6
00:00:20,938 --> 00:00:23,315
The assembled hoards of Genghis Khan
couldn't get through that door,

7
00:00:23,398 --> 00:00:24,775
and believe me, they've tried.

8
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:27,069
-Are you alien?
-Yes.

9
00:00:27,611 --> 00:00:29,071
(GRUNTING)

10
00:00:30,989 --> 00:00:32,074
You could come with me.

11
00:00:32,157 --> 00:00:34,409
-Is it always this dangerous?
-Yeah.

12
00:00:40,332 --> 00:00:41,375
(DOOR CLOSES)

13
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:43,919
Right, Rose Tyler,
you tell me, where do you wanna go?

14
00:00:44,002 --> 00:00:48,298
Backwards or forwards in time?
It's your choice. What's it gonna be?

15
00:00:49,841 --> 00:00:51,009
Forwards.

16
00:00:54,388 --> 00:00:55,722
(TARDIS POWERING UP)

17
00:00:55,806 --> 00:00:58,600
-How far?
-One hundred years.

18
00:01:02,938 --> 00:01:04,356
(RUMBLING)

19
00:01:09,278 --> 00:01:12,447
There you go! Step outside those
doors, it's the 22nd century.

20
00:01:12,614 --> 00:01:14,157
-You're kidding.
-That's a bit boring, though.

21
00:01:14,241 --> 00:01:15,325
Do you wanna go further?

22
00:01:15,492 --> 00:01:16,660
Fine by me.

23
00:01:20,289 --> 00:01:22,416
(RUMBLING)

24
00:01:24,835 --> 00:01:27,254
Ten thousand years
in the future.

25
00:01:27,337 --> 00:01:31,675
Step outside,
it's the year 12005. The new Roman Empire.

26
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:33,635
You think
you're so impressive.

27
00:01:33,719 --> 00:01:35,887
-I am so impressive.
-You wish!

28
00:01:36,221 --> 00:01:39,725
Right, then. You asked for it.
I know exactly where to go.

29
00:01:43,228 --> 00:01:44,438
Hold on!

30
00:01:44,521 --> 00:01:46,189
(RUMBLING)

31
00:01:56,241 --> 00:01:57,492
(DINGS)

32
00:02:00,287 --> 00:02:02,039
Where are we?

33
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:03,582
(METALLIC CREAKING)

34
00:02:04,583 --> 00:02:06,335
What's out there?

35
00:02:16,386 --> 00:02:18,013
(MACHINE HUMMING)

36
00:02:27,022 --> 00:02:28,690
(KEYS BLEEPING)

37
00:02:37,407 --> 00:02:41,620
You lot...
You spend all your time thinking about dying.

38
00:02:41,703 --> 00:02:46,416
How you're gonna get killed by eggs or beef
or global warming or asteroids.

39
00:02:47,084 --> 00:02:49,961
But you never take time
to imagine the impossible.

40
00:02:50,045 --> 00:02:51,797
That maybe you survived.

41
00:02:54,132 --> 00:02:57,969
This is the year 5.5/Apple/26.

42
00:02:58,053 --> 00:03:00,138
Five billion years
in your future.

43
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:02,766
And this is the day...

44
00:03:02,974 --> 00:03:04,393
Hold on...

45
00:03:11,608 --> 00:03:13,735
This is the day
the sun expands.

46
00:03:15,654 --> 00:03:18,031
Welcome to
the end of the world.

47
00:03:22,369 --> 00:03:24,413
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

48
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:12,794
AUTOMATED VOICE: Shuttles
five and six now docking.

49
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:15,881
Guests are reminded
that Platform One

50
00:04:15,964 --> 00:04:19,676
forbids the use of weapons,
teleportation and religion.

51
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:23,680
Earth-death
ls scheduled for 715:39,

52
00:04:23,764 --> 00:04:26,641
followed by drinks
in the Manchester Suite.

53
00:04:27,392 --> 00:04:30,228
ROSE: So when it says
"guests”, does that mean people?

54
00:04:30,312 --> 00:04:31,772
Depends what you mean
by people.

55
00:04:31,855 --> 00:04:34,733
-I mean people. What do you mean?
-Aliens.

56
00:04:35,609 --> 00:04:38,653
What are they doing
on board this spaceship? What's it all for?

57
00:04:38,737 --> 00:04:41,823
It's not really a spaceship,
more like an observation deck.

58
00:04:41,907 --> 00:04:44,951
The great and the good
are gathering to watch the planet burn.

59
00:04:45,035 --> 00:04:46,661
-What for?
-Fun!

60
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:54,294
Mind you, when I say "the great and the
good”, what I mean is the rich.

61
00:04:54,377 --> 00:04:59,090
But... Hold on, they did this
once on Newsround Extra, the sun expanding,

62
00:04:59,174 --> 00:05:01,676
-that takes hundreds of years.
-Millions.

63
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:03,804
But the planet's now
the property of the National Trust.

64
00:05:03,887 --> 00:05:05,013
They've been
keeping it preserved.

65
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:08,934
See down there?
Gravity satellites holding back the sun.

66
00:05:09,768 --> 00:05:11,228
The planet looks
the same as ever.

67
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:13,522
I thought the continent
shifted and things.

68
00:05:13,605 --> 00:05:16,733
They did, and the Trust
shifted 'em back! That's a classic Earth.

69
00:05:16,817 --> 00:05:19,903
But now
the money's run out, nature takes over.

70
00:05:20,946 --> 00:05:22,239
How long's it got?

71
00:05:23,198 --> 00:05:25,700
About half an hour.
Then the planet gets roasted.

72
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:29,996
Is that why we're here?
I mean, is that what you do?

73
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:32,499
Jump in at the last minute
and save the Earth?

74
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:34,918
I'm not saving it. Time's up.

75
00:05:35,418 --> 00:05:39,005
-But what about the people?
-It's empty. They've all gone. All left.

76
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:45,929
-Just me, then.
-Who the hell are you?

77
00:05:46,054 --> 00:05:49,057
-Oh, that's nice. Thanks.
-But how did you get in?

78
00:05:49,391 --> 00:05:51,852
This is a maximum
hospitality zone.

79
00:05:51,935 --> 00:05:54,604
The guests have disembarked!
They're on their way any second...

80
00:05:54,729 --> 00:05:57,107
No! That's me. I'm a guest.
Look, I've got an invitation.

81
00:05:57,232 --> 00:05:59,276
Look, there you see?
It's fine. You see?

82
00:05:59,359 --> 00:06:00,443
"The Doctor, plus one.”

83
00:06:00,527 --> 00:06:03,029
I'm the Doctor,
this is Rose Tyler, she's my "plus one".

84
00:06:03,113 --> 00:06:04,531
Is that all right?

85
00:06:04,614 --> 00:06:06,449
Well, obviously.

86
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:09,369
Apologies, et cetera.

87
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:12,205
If you're on board,
we'd better start.

88
00:06:13,415 --> 00:06:15,083
Enjoy.

89
00:06:16,293 --> 00:06:19,629
The paper's slightly psychic.
It shows them whatever I want them to see.

90
00:06:19,921 --> 00:06:21,631
Saves a lot of time.

91
00:06:21,756 --> 00:06:23,800
-He's blue.
-Yeah.

92
00:06:23,967 --> 00:06:25,051
Okay.

93
00:06:25,135 --> 00:06:28,889
We have in attendance,
the Doctor and Rose Tyler!

94
00:06:28,972 --> 00:06:31,808
Thank you.
All staff to their positions.

95
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:36,938
Hurry now! Thank you!
Quick as we can, come along, come along!

96
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:41,151
And now, might I introduce
the next honoured guest

97
00:06:41,276 --> 00:06:45,906
representing
the Forest of Cheem, we have trees.

98
00:06:46,281 --> 00:06:49,159
Namely Jabe, Lute and Coffa.

99
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:53,163
There will be an exchange
of gifts, representing peace.

100
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:55,790
If you could keep the room
circulating, thank you.

101
00:06:56,166 --> 00:07:02,172
Next, from the solicitors Jolco and Jolco, we
have the Moxx of Balhoon.

102
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:05,675
And next,
from Financial Family Seven,

103
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:08,762
we have the Adherents
of the Repeated Meme.

104
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:14,768
The inventors of hyposlip travel systems, the
brothers Hop Pyleen! Thank you.

105
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:16,353
Cal "Sparkplug"...

106
00:07:16,478 --> 00:07:18,021
Mr and Mrs Pakoo.

107
00:07:18,146 --> 00:07:21,191
The ambassadors from
the City State of Binding Light...

108
00:07:22,192 --> 00:07:27,030
The gift of peace. I bring you
a cutting of my grandfather.

109
00:07:28,615 --> 00:07:32,285
Thank you.
Yes, gifts, um... (CLEARS THROAT)

110
00:07:32,369 --> 00:07:35,956
I give you in return
air from my lungs.

111
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:41,795
How intimate.

112
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:43,546
There's more
where that came from.

113
00:07:44,547 --> 00:07:45,882
I bet there is.

114
00:07:47,884 --> 00:07:51,471
The sponsor
of the main event, please welcome...

115
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:53,223
the Face of Boe.

116
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,312
The Moxx of Balhoon.

117
00:07:59,396 --> 00:08:02,565
My felicitations upon this
historical happenstance.

118
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:04,651
I bring you the gift
of bodily salivas.

119
00:08:04,734 --> 00:08:06,569
(HAWKS AND SPITS)

120
00:08:06,695 --> 00:08:07,988
Thank you very much.

121
00:08:09,823 --> 00:08:12,909
Ah! The Adherents
of the Repeated Meme!

122
00:08:12,993 --> 00:08:15,078
I bring you air from my lungs.

123
00:08:15,829 --> 00:08:17,580
(EXHALES)

124
00:08:18,915 --> 00:08:21,584
A gift of peace.
In all good faith.

125
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:25,588
STEWARD:
And last but not least, our very special guest.

126
00:08:25,714 --> 00:08:31,845
Ladies and gentlemen and trees and
multiforms, consider the Earth, below.

127
00:08:32,429 --> 00:08:36,725
In memory of this dying world,
we call forth...

128
00:08:37,434 --> 00:08:39,602
the last human.

129
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:44,733
The Lady Cassandra O'Brien
Dot Delta Seventeen.

130
00:08:45,442 --> 00:08:49,612
Oh, now don't stare!
I know, I know. It's shocking, isn't it?

131
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:54,784
I've had my chin completely taken
away and look at the difference!

132
00:08:54,909 --> 00:08:59,706
Look how thin I am.
Thin and dainty!

133
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:02,292
I don't look a day over 2,000.

134
00:09:03,460 --> 00:09:05,754
Moisturise me, moisturise me!

135
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:09,924
Truly, I am the last human.

136
00:09:10,467 --> 00:09:15,055
My father was a Texan,
my mother was from the Arctic desert.

137
00:09:16,056 --> 00:09:18,641
They were born on the Earth

138
00:09:18,767 --> 00:09:22,437
and they were the last
to be buried in its soil.

139
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:28,818
(SNIFFLING) I have come
to honour them and say goodbye.

140
00:09:30,153 --> 00:09:32,781
Oh, no tears, no tears...

141
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:34,908
I'm sorry.

142
00:09:37,077 --> 00:09:40,497
But behold!
I bring gifts!

143
00:09:40,955 --> 00:09:45,794
From Earth itself,
the last remaining ostrich egg.

144
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:50,173
Legend says, it had
a wingspan of 50 feet!

145
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:52,592
And blew fire
from its nostrils.

146
00:09:53,093 --> 00:09:54,761
Or was that my third husband?

147
00:09:54,844 --> 00:09:59,099
(LAUGHING)
Oh, no, oh, don't laugh, I'll get laughter-lines.

148
00:09:59,182 --> 00:10:01,267
No, stop!

149
00:10:03,019 --> 00:10:04,938
(CLEARING THROAT) Mercy!

150
00:10:05,355 --> 00:10:08,358
And here! Another rarity.

151
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:13,029
According to the archives,
this was called an iPod.

152
00:10:13,154 --> 00:10:17,367
It stores classical music from
humanity's greatest composers.

153
00:10:17,659 --> 00:10:18,910
Play on!

154
00:10:26,209 --> 00:10:28,461
(TAINTED LOVE PLAYING)

155
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:31,464
The refreshments
will now be served.

156
00:10:32,382 --> 00:10:34,467
Earth-death in 30 minutes.

157
00:10:34,551 --> 00:10:40,223
# Sometimes I feel
I've got to run away

158
00:10:40,306 --> 00:10:44,894
# I've got to get away
from the pain

159
00:10:44,978 --> 00:10:48,481
# That you drive
into the heart of me

160
00:10:48,565 --> 00:10:54,904
# The love we share
seems to go nowhere

161
00:10:55,029 --> 00:10:58,491
# And I've lost my light

162
00:10:58,575 --> 00:11:02,495
# For I toss and turn
I can't sleep at night... #

163
00:11:02,579 --> 00:11:05,248
-Doctor.
-(DEVICE CHIRPS)

164
00:11:05,331 --> 00:11:06,749
Thank you.

165
00:11:08,418 --> 00:11:11,337
A gift of peace
in all good faith.

166
00:11:11,421 --> 00:11:14,340
No, you're very kind,
but I'm just the steward.

167
00:11:14,424 --> 00:11:18,094
A gift of peace
in all good faith.

168
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:21,431
Oh, yes. Thank you.
Of course.

169
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:23,433
Identify species.

170
00:11:24,058 --> 00:11:25,852
(DEVICE CHIRPING)

171
00:11:25,935 --> 00:11:28,062
Please identify species.

172
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:29,939
-(WHISTLING)
-Now stop it!

173
00:11:30,023 --> 00:11:32,775
Identify his race.
Where's he from?

174
00:11:32,901 --> 00:11:34,944
(DEVICE TWITTERING)

175
00:11:36,529 --> 00:11:38,239
It's impossible.

176
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:11,064
ROSE: Sorry, am I allowed
to be in here?

177
00:12:11,814 --> 00:12:14,609
You have to give us
permission to talk.

178
00:12:16,319 --> 00:12:17,987
Um...

179
00:12:19,489 --> 00:12:23,326
-You have permission.
-Thank you.

180
00:12:24,118 --> 00:12:26,621
And, no,
you're not in the way.

181
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:29,374
-Guests are allowed anywhere.
-Okay.

182
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:32,460
(KEYS BLEEPING)

183
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:36,839
-What's your name?
-Raffalo.

184
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:39,717
-Raffalo?
-Yes, miss.

185
00:12:40,927 --> 00:12:44,180
I won't be long, I've just got
to carry out some maintenance.

186
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:48,434
There's a tiny little glitch
in the Face of Boe's suite.

187
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:50,979
There must be something
blocking the system.

188
00:12:51,062 --> 00:12:53,439
He's not getting
any hot water.

189
00:12:54,274 --> 00:12:57,527
-So, you're a plumber?
-That's right, miss.

190
00:12:58,945 --> 00:13:00,947
They still have plumbers?

191
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:02,949
I hope so,
else I'm out of a job!

192
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:07,245
-Where are you from?
-Crespallion.

193
00:13:09,122 --> 00:13:11,416
ROSE: That's a planet, is it?

194
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:14,711
No, Crespallion's part of
the Jaggit Brocade,

195
00:13:14,794 --> 00:13:17,839
affiliated to the
Scarlet Junction, Convex 56.

196
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:21,301
And where are you from, miss?
If you don't mind me asking.

197
00:13:21,426 --> 00:13:23,594
No, not at all. Um...

198
00:13:24,929 --> 00:13:28,057
I don't know. A long way away.

199
00:13:29,642 --> 00:13:32,812
I just sort of hitched a lift
with this man...

200
00:13:34,272 --> 00:13:38,818
I didn't even think about it.
Don't even know who he is.

201
00:13:41,362 --> 00:13:43,448
He's a complete stranger.

202
00:13:45,158 --> 00:13:48,703
Anyway,
don't let me keep you. Good luck with it!

203
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:54,125
Thank you, miss.
And thank you for the permission.

204
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:56,377
Not many people are
that considerate.

205
00:13:56,461 --> 00:13:58,296
Okay. See you later.

206
00:14:06,721 --> 00:14:08,139
Now, then.

207
00:14:08,222 --> 00:14:11,893
Control, I'm at junction 19.
I think the problem's coming from in here.

208
00:14:11,976 --> 00:14:13,895
I'll go inside
and have a look.

209
00:14:13,978 --> 00:14:15,104
(LIGHT CLANKING)

210
00:14:15,188 --> 00:14:18,316
What's that?
Something in there?

211
00:14:19,067 --> 00:14:20,985
Ooh. Who are you, then?

212
00:14:21,402 --> 00:14:22,570
Hold on!

213
00:14:24,238 --> 00:14:27,575
If you're an upgrade,
I just need to register you, that's all.

214
00:14:27,658 --> 00:14:29,118
Oh, come back.

215
00:14:30,328 --> 00:14:32,705
Ah, there you are.

216
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:35,541
Now, I just need
to register your ident.

217
00:14:36,918 --> 00:14:41,255
Aw, there's two of ya!
Got yourself a little mate?

218
00:14:43,466 --> 00:14:46,260
I think I'd better
report this to control.

219
00:14:46,344 --> 00:14:48,721
How many of you are there?

220
00:14:50,098 --> 00:14:51,516
What are you?

221
00:14:52,433 --> 00:14:55,186
Oh, no! No! (SCREAMING)

222
00:15:05,947 --> 00:15:07,281
(BLEEPING)

223
00:15:07,365 --> 00:15:09,325
-What's that?
-(BLEEPS)

224
00:15:09,409 --> 00:15:11,786
-Well, how should I know?
-(BLEEPS)

225
00:15:14,288 --> 00:15:18,543
(OVER PA) Would the owner
of the blue box in private gallery 15

226
00:15:18,626 --> 00:15:21,087
please report to
the steward's office immediately.

227
00:15:22,547 --> 00:15:26,592
Guests are reminded
that the use of teleportation devices

228
00:15:26,676 --> 00:15:32,223
is strictly prohibited under
Peace Treaty 5.4/Cup/16. Thank you.

229
00:15:32,432 --> 00:15:35,977
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Earth-death in 25 minutes.

230
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:39,063
Earth-death in 25 minutes.

231
00:15:39,147 --> 00:15:41,232
Oh, thanks.

232
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:48,990
Hello!

233
00:15:49,407 --> 00:15:52,869
My name's Rose.
That's a sort of plant.

234
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:55,913
We might be related.

235
00:15:57,874 --> 00:15:59,834
I'm talking to a twig.

236
00:16:08,009 --> 00:16:09,844
(GRUNTING)

237
00:16:11,262 --> 00:16:14,974
Oi, now, careful with that,
park it properly. No scratches.

238
00:16:17,685 --> 00:16:19,812
(SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE)

239
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:40,583
DOCTOR:
Rose, are you in there?

240
00:16:42,877 --> 00:16:44,212
Aye-aye!

241
00:16:46,589 --> 00:16:49,884
-What do you think, then?
-Great, yeah. Fine.

242
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:52,887
Once you get past
the slightly psychic paper.

243
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:54,388
(CHUCKLES)

244
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:57,767
They're just so alien!

245
00:16:59,852 --> 00:17:02,396
The aliens are so alien.

246
00:17:04,232 --> 00:17:07,193
You look at 'em,
and they're alien.

247
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:09,779
Good thing I didn't take you
to the deep south.

248
00:17:12,365 --> 00:17:15,493
-Where are you from?
-All over the place.

249
00:17:16,786 --> 00:17:19,455
-They all speak English.
-No, you just hear English.

250
00:17:19,539 --> 00:17:21,791
It's a gift of the Tardis.
It's the telepathic field,

251
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:24,001
gets inside your brain,
translates.

252
00:17:24,085 --> 00:17:27,046
-It's inside my brain?
-Well, in a good way.

253
00:17:27,672 --> 00:17:29,799
Your machine gets
inside my head?

254
00:17:29,882 --> 00:17:33,344
It gets inside and it changes my
mind and you didn't even ask.

255
00:17:33,803 --> 00:17:35,388
I didn't think
about it like that.

256
00:17:35,471 --> 00:17:38,891
No, you were too busy thinking up cheap
shots about the deep south!

257
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:42,103
Who are you then, Doctor.

258
00:17:42,895 --> 00:17:45,064
What're you called?
What sort of alien are you?

259
00:17:45,147 --> 00:17:47,650
-I'm just a Doctor.
-From what planet?

260
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:49,527
(SNIGGERS)
Well, it's not as if you'd know where it is.

261
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:51,529
-Where're you from?
-What does it matter?

262
00:17:51,612 --> 00:17:53,447
-Tell me who you are!
-This is who I am.

263
00:17:53,531 --> 00:17:55,074
Right here, right now.
All right?

264
00:17:55,157 --> 00:17:57,910
All that counts
is here and now, and this is me!

265
00:17:57,994 --> 00:18:02,290
Yeah, and I'm here too
"cause you brought me here! So just tell me!

266
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:13,926
Earth-death in 20 minutes.

267
00:18:15,386 --> 00:18:18,806
Earth-death in 20 minutes.

268
00:18:26,397 --> 00:18:27,857
All right.

269
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:32,069
As my mate Shireen says,

270
00:18:32,153 --> 00:18:35,031
"Don't argue with
the designated driver."

271
00:18:37,199 --> 00:18:39,118
Can't exactly call for a taxi.

272
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:40,244
(BEEPING)

273
00:18:40,328 --> 00:18:41,871
There's no signal.

274
00:18:42,872 --> 00:18:45,708
We're out of range.
Just a bit.

275
00:18:47,877 --> 00:18:51,172
Tell you what,
with a little bit of jiggery-pokery...

276
00:18:51,255 --> 00:18:53,507
Is that a technical term,
"jiggery-pokery"?

277
00:18:53,591 --> 00:18:55,885
Yeah, I came first
in jiggery-pokery. What about you?

278
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:58,512
-No, I failed hullabaloo.
-Aw.

279
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:02,767
There you go.

280
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:08,064
(BEEPS)

281
00:19:10,775 --> 00:19:12,443
(RINGING TONE)

282
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:17,031
-Hello?
-Mum?

283
00:19:17,114 --> 00:19:20,493
Oh, what is it?
What's wrong? What have I done now?

284
00:19:20,576 --> 00:19:24,163
Ooh, this red top's falling
to bits! You should get your money back.

285
00:19:24,246 --> 00:19:26,123
Go on,
there must be something.

286
00:19:26,207 --> 00:19:27,917
You never phone
in the middle of the day.

287
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,294
-(CHUCKLES)
-What's so funny?

288
00:19:30,378 --> 00:19:32,421
Nothing.
You all right, though?

289
00:19:32,505 --> 00:19:34,090
Yeah, why wouldn't I be?

290
00:19:34,674 --> 00:19:39,345
-What day is it?
-Wednesday all day. You got a hangover?

291
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:42,056
Oh, I tell you what,
put a quid in that lottery syndicate.

292
00:19:42,139 --> 00:19:43,557
I'll pay you back later.

293
00:19:43,641 --> 00:19:48,354
Yeah, um, I was just calling
'cause I might be late home.

294
00:19:48,729 --> 00:19:49,939
Is there something wrong?

295
00:19:50,231 --> 00:19:54,151
No, I'm fine.
Top of the world!

296
00:19:59,156 --> 00:20:02,702
If you think that's amazing,
you wanna see the bill.

297
00:20:02,785 --> 00:20:05,204
That was five billion
years ago.

298
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:07,623
So...

299
00:20:07,707 --> 00:20:09,250
She's dead now.

300
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:14,463
Five billion years later,
my mum's dead.

301
00:20:14,588 --> 00:20:16,382
Bundle of laughs, you are.

302
00:20:17,007 --> 00:20:18,884
(RUMBLING)

303
00:20:21,679 --> 00:20:23,764
That's not supposed to happen.

304
00:20:23,848 --> 00:20:27,601
Well, what was it?
I'm just getting green lights at this end.

305
00:20:27,685 --> 00:20:29,979
(OVER PA) Honoured guests
may be reassured

306
00:20:30,062 --> 00:20:34,483
that gravity pockets
may cause slight turbulence. Thanking you.

307
00:20:34,567 --> 00:20:37,445
The whole place shook!
I felt it!

308
00:20:37,528 --> 00:20:41,240
I've hosted all sorts of events on platforms
one, three, six and fifteen

309
00:20:41,323 --> 00:20:43,534
and I've never felt
the slightest tremor!

310
00:20:43,617 --> 00:20:46,495
I warn you, if this lot
decide to sue...

311
00:20:46,579 --> 00:20:48,372
I'm gonna scan
the infrastructure.

312
00:20:50,374 --> 00:20:51,917
(MACHINE BLEEPING)

313
00:20:53,794 --> 00:20:55,463
What's that?

314
00:20:56,547 --> 00:20:59,467
Control, I don't want to worry
you, but I'm picking up readings...

315
00:20:59,550 --> 00:21:01,010
(BLEEPING)

316
00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:05,806
I have no idea! They're small.
The scan says they're metal...

317
00:21:05,890 --> 00:21:08,392
-(BLEEPS)
-I don't know what they look like!

318
00:21:11,270 --> 00:21:15,065
Although I imagine they might
look rather like that.

319
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:22,865
You're not on the guest list.
How did you get on board?

320
00:21:25,242 --> 00:21:26,660
(BEEPS)

321
00:21:27,912 --> 00:21:30,873
-No! No!
-AUTOMATED VOICE: Sunfilter deactivated.

322
00:21:31,123 --> 00:21:33,167
Sunfilter descending.

323
00:21:33,334 --> 00:21:34,585
Sunfilter up! No, no, no!

324
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:37,421
External temperature
430 degrees.

325
00:21:37,546 --> 00:21:39,340
-Control! Respond!
-Sunfilter descending.

326
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:41,759
-Sunfilter up!
-Sunfilter descending.

327
00:21:41,884 --> 00:21:43,886
(SCREAMING)

328
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:04,323
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

329
00:22:08,244 --> 00:22:12,289
That wasn't a gravity pocket. I know gravity
pockets, and they don't feel like that.

330
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:14,375
What do you think, Jabe?

331
00:22:14,458 --> 00:22:16,627
Listen to the engines,
they're pitched up about 30 Hertz.

332
00:22:16,752 --> 00:22:18,337
Is that dodgy or what?

333
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:21,090
It's the sound of metal,
that doesn't make any sense to me.

334
00:22:21,841 --> 00:22:24,844
-Where's the engine room?
-I don't know.

335
00:22:25,177 --> 00:22:28,722
But the maintenance duct is just behind our
guests' suite, I could show you.

336
00:22:28,806 --> 00:22:31,141
And your wife.

337
00:22:31,267 --> 00:22:32,726
Oh, she's not my wife.

338
00:22:32,810 --> 00:22:34,478
-Partner?
-No.

339
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:36,939
-Concubine?
-Nope.

340
00:22:37,022 --> 00:22:38,107
Prostitute?

341
00:22:39,358 --> 00:22:42,152
Whatever I am,
it must be invisible! Do you mind?

342
00:22:42,778 --> 00:22:44,989
Tell you what,
you two go and pollinate.

343
00:22:45,114 --> 00:22:46,907
I'm gonna catch up
with the Family.

344
00:22:46,991 --> 00:22:48,868
Quick word
with Michael Jackson.

345
00:22:49,451 --> 00:22:51,245
Don't start a fight.

346
00:22:51,328 --> 00:22:53,038
I'm all yours.

347
00:22:55,875 --> 00:22:57,501
And I want you home
by midnight!

348
00:22:59,044 --> 00:23:04,341
AUTOMATED VOICE: Earth-death in 15
minutes. Earth-death in 15 minutes.

349
00:23:14,476 --> 00:23:17,855
Who's in charge
of Platform One? Has it got a captain or what?

350
00:23:17,980 --> 00:23:20,232
There's just the steward
and the staff.

351
00:23:20,316 --> 00:23:22,860
All the rest is controlled
by the metal mind.

352
00:23:22,985 --> 00:23:25,446
You mean, the computer?
Well, who controls that?

353
00:23:25,529 --> 00:23:26,989
The Corporation.

354
00:23:27,072 --> 00:23:30,868
They move Platform One
from one artistic event to another.

355
00:23:31,493 --> 00:23:33,579
Well, there's no one
from the Corporation on board.

356
00:23:33,662 --> 00:23:37,541
They're not needed.
This facility is purely automatic.

357
00:23:37,666 --> 00:23:39,376
It's the height of
the Alpha Class.

358
00:23:39,501 --> 00:23:41,962
-Nothing can go wrong.
-Unsinkable?

359
00:23:42,046 --> 00:23:45,299
If you like. The nautical
metaphor is appropriate.

360
00:23:45,382 --> 00:23:47,509
You're telling me!
I was on board another ship once.

361
00:23:47,635 --> 00:23:49,053
They said that was unsinkable.

362
00:23:49,178 --> 00:23:52,723
I ended up
clinging to an iceberg. It wasn't half cold.

363
00:23:52,848 --> 00:23:57,978
So, what you're saying is, if we get in
trouble, there's no one to help us out?

364
00:23:58,062 --> 00:24:00,564
-I'm afraid not.
-Fantastic!

365
00:24:01,565 --> 00:24:05,361
I don't understand.
In what way is that fantastic?

366
00:24:11,075 --> 00:24:14,995
CASSANDRA: Soon the sun
will blossom into a red giant,

367
00:24:15,079 --> 00:24:17,039
and my home will die.

368
00:24:17,164 --> 00:24:20,709
That's where I used to live,
when I was a little boy. Down there.

369
00:24:20,834 --> 00:24:24,880
Mummy and Daddy had a house built into the
side of the Los Angeles Crevasse.

370
00:24:25,005 --> 00:24:27,341
(SIGHS) I'd have such fun.

371
00:24:27,758 --> 00:24:29,510
What happened
to everyone else?

372
00:24:29,593 --> 00:24:31,720
The human race,
where did it go?

373
00:24:32,596 --> 00:24:36,475
They say mankind has touched
every star in the sky.

374
00:24:36,558 --> 00:24:38,394
So you're not the last human.

375
00:24:39,019 --> 00:24:42,231
I am the last pure human.

376
00:24:43,023 --> 00:24:45,275
The others mingled.

377
00:24:45,776 --> 00:24:48,570
Oh, they call themselves
New-humans and Proto-humans

378
00:24:48,696 --> 00:24:50,739
and Digi-humans,
even Human-ish!

379
00:24:50,864 --> 00:24:53,367
But do you know
what I call them?

380
00:24:53,450 --> 00:24:54,785
Mongrels.

381
00:24:55,536 --> 00:24:58,080
Right. And you stayed behind.

382
00:24:58,539 --> 00:25:01,041
-I kept myself pure.
-Hmm.

383
00:25:01,583 --> 00:25:03,711
How many operations
have you had?

384
00:25:04,044 --> 00:25:09,049
708. Next week, it's 709.
I'm having my blood bleached.

385
00:25:10,592 --> 00:25:12,469
Is that why you wanted a word?

386
00:25:12,886 --> 00:25:15,055
You could be flatter, Rose.

387
00:25:15,139 --> 00:25:18,267
You've got a little bit
of a chin poking out.

388
00:25:18,392 --> 00:25:21,729
-I'd rather die.
-Honestly, it doesn't hurt.

389
00:25:22,229 --> 00:25:24,356
I mean it. I would rather die.

390
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:28,652
It's better to die
than to live like you, a bitchy trampoline.

391
00:25:28,777 --> 00:25:31,280
Oh, well, what do you know?

392
00:25:32,114 --> 00:25:34,199
I was born on that planet!

393
00:25:34,283 --> 00:25:36,702
And so was my mum
and so was my dad.

394
00:25:36,785 --> 00:25:39,788
And that makes me, officially,
the last human being in this room.

395
00:25:39,913 --> 00:25:41,790
'Cause you're not human.

396
00:25:41,957 --> 00:25:46,003
You've had it all nipped and tucked and
flattened till there's nothing left.

397
00:25:46,128 --> 00:25:47,921
Anything human
got chucked in the bin!

398
00:25:48,005 --> 00:25:51,341
You're just skin, Cassandra!
Lipstick and skin.

399
00:25:52,134 --> 00:25:53,635
Nice talking.

400
00:26:01,643 --> 00:26:06,565
So, tell me, Jabe, what's a tree like
you doing in a place like this?

401
00:26:06,648 --> 00:26:08,734
-Respect for the Earth.
-Come on!

402
00:26:08,817 --> 00:26:11,153
Everyone on this platform is worth zillions!

403
00:26:11,236 --> 00:26:15,741
Well, perhaps it's a case of
having to be seen at the right occasions.

404
00:26:15,824 --> 00:26:17,659
In case
your share prices drop?

405
00:26:17,743 --> 00:26:21,330
I know you lot. You've got massive forests
everywhere, roots everywhere!

406
00:26:21,413 --> 00:26:23,499
And there's
always money in land.

407
00:26:23,624 --> 00:26:25,250
All the same.

408
00:26:25,334 --> 00:26:27,920
We respect
the Earth as family.

409
00:26:28,003 --> 00:26:31,924
So many species
evolved from that planet. Mankind is only one.

410
00:26:32,007 --> 00:26:33,425
I am another.

411
00:26:33,509 --> 00:26:37,012
My ancestors were transplanted
from the planet down below.

412
00:26:37,096 --> 00:26:40,265
And I'm a direct descendant
of the tropical rain forest.

413
00:26:40,349 --> 00:26:42,184
Excuse me.

414
00:26:44,937 --> 00:26:47,147
And what about your ancestry,
Doctor?

415
00:26:49,024 --> 00:26:51,819
Perhaps you could tell
a story or two.

416
00:26:53,529 --> 00:26:58,700
Perhaps a man only enjoys trouble
when there's nothing else left?

417
00:27:00,536 --> 00:27:02,538
I scanned you earlier.

418
00:27:03,956 --> 00:27:06,959
The metal machine had trouble
identifying your species.

419
00:27:07,042 --> 00:27:08,877
It refused to admit
your existence.

420
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:12,631
And even when it named you,
I wouldn't believe it.

421
00:27:12,965 --> 00:27:14,675
But it was right.

422
00:27:15,884 --> 00:27:18,137
I know where you're from!

423
00:27:20,347 --> 00:27:24,393
Forgive me for intruding,
but it's remarkable that you even exist!

424
00:27:26,019 --> 00:27:28,063
I just want to say...

425
00:27:29,356 --> 00:27:31,400
how sorry I am.

426
00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:55,424
(SLOW CHUFFING)

427
00:28:02,848 --> 00:28:05,225
Is it me,
or is it a bit nippy?

428
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,950
(GROANS)

429
00:28:28,415 --> 00:28:30,792
Fair dos, though,
that's a great bit of air-conditioning.

430
00:28:30,876 --> 00:28:32,544
Sort of nice
and old fashioned.

431
00:28:32,628 --> 00:28:34,129
Bet they call it retro.

432
00:28:34,296 --> 00:28:35,964
(WHINING)

433
00:28:36,089 --> 00:28:37,633
Gotcha!

434
00:28:43,805 --> 00:28:47,476
-What the hell is that?
-Is it part of the "retro"?

435
00:28:47,601 --> 00:28:49,811
I don't think so, hold on.

436
00:28:57,152 --> 00:29:00,489
-Hey, nice Liana!
-Thank you.

437
00:29:00,572 --> 00:29:02,241
Not supposed to
show them in public.

438
00:29:02,324 --> 00:29:04,660
Don't worry,
I won't tell anybody.

439
00:29:04,743 --> 00:29:07,537
Now, then, who's been
bringing their pets on board?

440
00:29:07,621 --> 00:29:09,748
-What does it do?
-Sabotage...

441
00:29:09,831 --> 00:29:12,251
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Earth-death in 10 minutes...

442
00:29:12,334 --> 00:29:15,003
And the temperature's
about to rocket. Come on.

443
00:29:16,964 --> 00:29:19,383
The planet's end!

444
00:29:19,466 --> 00:29:21,927
Come gather, come gather!

445
00:29:22,010 --> 00:29:25,639
Bid farewell to the cradle
of civilisation.

446
00:29:25,722 --> 00:29:29,393
Let us mourn her
with a traditional ballad.

447
00:29:32,396 --> 00:29:34,523
(TOXIC PLAYING)

448
00:29:36,358 --> 00:29:39,945
# Baby, can't you see?
I'm calling

449
00:29:40,028 --> 00:29:43,448
# A guy like you
should wear a warning

450
00:29:43,532 --> 00:29:46,576
# It's dangerous
I'm fallin'... #

451
00:29:46,660 --> 00:29:48,537
All right, hold on, get back!

452
00:29:48,620 --> 00:29:50,163
(ALARM WAILING)

453
00:29:51,790 --> 00:29:55,711
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Sunfilter rising. Sunfilter rising.

454
00:29:55,794 --> 00:29:58,005
-Is the steward in there?
-You can smell him.

455
00:29:58,088 --> 00:29:59,256
(ALARM BEEPING)

456
00:29:59,339 --> 00:30:02,342
Hold on. There's another
sun filter programed to descend.

457
00:30:04,303 --> 00:30:07,514
# Too high can't come down

458
00:30:07,597 --> 00:30:12,936
# Losing my head
Spinning round and round

459
00:30:13,020 --> 00:30:14,938
# Do you feel me now? #

460
00:30:15,022 --> 00:30:20,110
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Sunfilter descending. Sunfilter descending.

461
00:30:25,615 --> 00:30:27,868
Sunfilter descending.

462
00:30:27,951 --> 00:30:30,829
-Let me out! Let me out!
-Sunfilter descending.

463
00:30:31,788 --> 00:30:33,540
(BANGING ON DOOR)

464
00:30:33,623 --> 00:30:36,001
ROSE: Let me out!
Let me out! Let me out!

465
00:30:36,084 --> 00:30:41,006
Sunfilter descending.
Sunfilter descending.

466
00:30:41,089 --> 00:30:42,799
-(BANGING CONTINUES)
-Anyone in there?

467
00:30:42,883 --> 00:30:45,927
-Let me out!
-Oh, well, it would be you.

468
00:30:46,011 --> 00:30:48,972
-Open the door!
-Hold on, give us two ticks.

469
00:30:49,181 --> 00:30:54,394
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Sunfilter descending. Sunfilter descending.

470
00:30:54,519 --> 00:30:55,771
(BEEPING)

471
00:30:55,854 --> 00:30:59,775
Sunfilter rising.
Sunfilter rising.

472
00:31:01,443 --> 00:31:06,114
Sunfilter rising.
Sunfilter rising...

473
00:31:06,198 --> 00:31:08,283
Sunfilter descending.

474
00:31:08,867 --> 00:31:11,453
It's just what I need.
The computer's getting clever.

475
00:31:11,536 --> 00:31:15,457
-Stop mucking about!
-I'm not mucking about! It's fighting back.

476
00:31:15,582 --> 00:31:17,209
-Sunfilter descending.
-Open the door!

477
00:31:17,292 --> 00:31:18,335
DOCTOR: I know!

478
00:31:18,418 --> 00:31:22,255
-Sunfilter descending.
-ROSE: The lock's melted!

479
00:31:23,799 --> 00:31:28,762
Sunfilter descending.
Sunfilter descending.

480
00:31:32,391 --> 00:31:36,144
Sunfilter rising.
Sunfilter rising.

481
00:31:37,771 --> 00:31:39,189
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

482
00:31:42,818 --> 00:31:46,321
The opening's jammed!
I can't open the door. Stay there, don't move!

483
00:31:46,405 --> 00:31:48,323
Where am I gonna go? Ipswich?

484
00:31:48,532 --> 00:31:50,992
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Earth-death in five minutes.

485
00:31:53,286 --> 00:31:55,705
The metal machine confirms...

486
00:31:55,789 --> 00:31:58,834
the spider devices
have infiltrated the whole of Platform One.

487
00:31:58,917 --> 00:32:00,168
(GUESTS GASP)

488
00:32:00,252 --> 00:32:03,422
How's that possible? Our private rooms
are protected by a code-wall.

489
00:32:03,505 --> 00:32:05,715
Moisturise me, moisturise me.

490
00:32:05,841 --> 00:32:07,717
Summon the steward!

491
00:32:07,801 --> 00:32:09,553
I'm afraid
the steward is dead.

492
00:32:09,845 --> 00:32:11,471
(ALL GASPING)

493
00:32:11,555 --> 00:32:13,140
(ALL MURMURING)

494
00:32:14,307 --> 00:32:15,851
Who killed him?

495
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:19,479
This whole event was sponsored
by the Face of Boe! He invited us.

496
00:32:19,563 --> 00:32:21,481
Talk to the face!
Talk to the face!

497
00:32:21,565 --> 00:32:24,651
Easy way of finding out.
Someone brought their little pet on board.

498
00:32:25,152 --> 00:32:26,528
Let's send him back to master.

499
00:32:33,910 --> 00:32:35,078
(BEEPING)

500
00:32:49,050 --> 00:32:52,262
The Adherents of
the Repeated Meme! f'accuse!

501
00:32:52,387 --> 00:32:55,015
That's all very well
and really kinda obvious.

502
00:32:55,098 --> 00:32:57,225
But if you stop
and think about it...

503
00:32:57,559 --> 00:32:58,935
(GROANS)

504
00:32:59,019 --> 00:33:01,271
A Repeated Meme
is just an idea.

505
00:33:01,521 --> 00:33:03,815
And that's all they are,
an idea.

506
00:33:03,899 --> 00:33:05,817
(POWERS DOWN)

507
00:33:07,819 --> 00:33:11,823
Remote-control droids.
Nice little cover for the real troublemaker.

508
00:33:12,282 --> 00:33:14,409
Go on, Jimbo. Go home.

509
00:33:17,245 --> 00:33:18,497
(GUESTS GASP)

510
00:33:18,580 --> 00:33:21,666
I bet you were the school swot
and never got kissed.

511
00:33:21,875 --> 00:33:23,210
At arms!

512
00:33:23,418 --> 00:33:25,003
What you gonna do,
moisturise me?

513
00:33:25,128 --> 00:33:26,463
With acid.

514
00:33:26,546 --> 00:33:28,298
Oh, you're too late anyway.

515
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:31,510
My spiders have control
of the main frame.

516
00:33:31,635 --> 00:33:36,640
Oh, you all carried them
as gifts, tax-free, past every code-wall.

517
00:33:37,974 --> 00:33:39,768
I'm not just a pretty face.

518
00:33:39,851 --> 00:33:42,771
Sabotaging a ship
while you're still inside it, how stupid is that?

519
00:33:42,938 --> 00:33:45,899
I'd hoped to manufacture
a hostage situation.

520
00:33:45,982 --> 00:33:48,026
With myself
as one of the victims.

521
00:33:48,818 --> 00:33:51,655
The compensation
would've been enormous.

522
00:33:51,780 --> 00:33:54,407
Five billion years,
and it still comes down to money.

523
00:33:54,824 --> 00:33:57,410
Do you think it's cheap,
looking like this?

524
00:33:57,494 --> 00:33:59,996
Flatness costs a fortune!

525
00:34:01,164 --> 00:34:02,916
I am the last human, Doctor.

526
00:34:03,750 --> 00:34:07,712
Me, not that
freaky little kid of yours.

527
00:34:07,879 --> 00:34:10,173
Arrest her! The infidel!

528
00:34:10,257 --> 00:34:14,553
Oh, shut it, pixie!
I've still got my final option.

529
00:34:14,636 --> 00:34:16,888
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Earth-death in three minutes.

530
00:34:16,972 --> 00:34:21,268
And here it comes.
You're just as useful dead, all of you.

531
00:34:21,851 --> 00:34:24,145
I have shares in
your rival companies.

532
00:34:24,229 --> 00:34:26,439
And they'll triple in price
as soon as your dead.

533
00:34:27,107 --> 00:34:30,610
My spiders are primed
and ready to destroy the safety systems.

534
00:34:30,944 --> 00:34:33,613
How did that
old Earth song go?

535
00:34:33,697 --> 00:34:35,198
"Burn baby, burn."

536
00:34:35,282 --> 00:34:36,866
Then you'll burn with us!

537
00:34:36,950 --> 00:34:39,119
Oh, I'm so sorry!

538
00:34:39,452 --> 00:34:44,207
I know the use
of teleportation is strictly forbidden, but...

539
00:34:44,291 --> 00:34:46,126
I'm such a naughty thing.

540
00:34:46,793 --> 00:34:48,753
Spiders, activate!

541
00:34:49,212 --> 00:34:51,006
(THUNDEROUS WHOOSHES)

542
00:34:58,388 --> 00:35:02,642
Force-fields gone,
with the planet about to explode...

543
00:35:02,726 --> 00:35:04,352
At least it'll be quick.

544
00:35:04,728 --> 00:35:07,272
Just like my fifth husband...
(LAUGHS)

545
00:35:07,355 --> 00:35:11,234
Oh, shame on me!
Bye-bye, darlings.

546
00:35:11,318 --> 00:35:14,112
-AUTOMATED VOICE: Safety systems failing.
-Bye-bye, my darlings!

547
00:35:14,738 --> 00:35:17,157
Heat levels rising.

548
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:19,951
-Reset the computer!
-Only the steward would know how.

549
00:35:20,035 --> 00:35:21,870
No, we can do it by hand.

550
00:35:21,953 --> 00:35:24,956
There must be
a system restore switch. Jabe, come on!

551
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:26,541
You lot, just chill.

552
00:35:26,666 --> 00:35:27,667
...Heat levels rising.

553
00:35:28,209 --> 00:35:30,170
(ALARM BLARING)

554
00:35:32,339 --> 00:35:37,135
Earth-death in two minutes.
Earth-death in two minutes.

555
00:35:39,012 --> 00:35:44,434
Heat levels critical
Heat levels critical

556
00:35:47,646 --> 00:35:50,065
Oh, and guess
where the switch is.

557
00:35:51,066 --> 00:35:55,028
Heat levels rising.
Heat levels rising.

558
00:35:56,279 --> 00:35:57,447
(GRUNTS)

559
00:36:04,954 --> 00:36:09,292
External temperature
5,000 degrees.

560
00:36:18,968 --> 00:36:21,888
You can't, the heat's gonna
vent through this place.

561
00:36:21,971 --> 00:36:24,182
-I know.
-Jabe, you're made of wood.

562
00:36:24,265 --> 00:36:27,435
Then stop wasting time,
Time Lord.

563
00:36:30,730 --> 00:36:34,818
Heat levels rising.
Heat levels rising.

564
00:36:34,901 --> 00:36:36,361
-(PANICKED GASPS)
-(WINDOW CRACKING)

565
00:36:36,444 --> 00:36:38,780
Heat levels hazardous.

566
00:36:38,863 --> 00:36:42,534
-We're going to die!
-Heat levels hazardous.

567
00:36:57,215 --> 00:36:59,801
Shields malfunction.

568
00:37:01,010 --> 00:37:03,430
Shields malfunction.

569
00:37:04,806 --> 00:37:08,309
Shields malfunction.

570
00:37:08,393 --> 00:37:11,229
-(GASPS)
-Shields malfunction.

571
00:37:16,818 --> 00:37:22,615
Heat levels critical
Heat levels critical

572
00:37:28,872 --> 00:37:30,623
(SCREAMING)

573
00:37:33,293 --> 00:37:34,377
(WHIMPERS)

574
00:37:35,336 --> 00:37:40,049
Heat levels rising.
Heat levels rising.

575
00:37:40,592 --> 00:37:42,719
(JABE SCREAMING)

576
00:38:07,619 --> 00:38:09,621
Planet explodes in...

577
00:38:10,538 --> 00:38:12,207
ten,

578
00:38:12,832 --> 00:38:14,417
nine,

579
00:38:16,044 --> 00:38:17,754
eight,

580
00:38:19,881 --> 00:38:21,424
seven,

581
00:38:23,301 --> 00:38:24,803
Six,

582
00:38:27,180 --> 00:38:28,640
five,

583
00:38:30,433 --> 00:38:31,935
four...

584
00:38:35,522 --> 00:38:36,815
Raise shields!

585
00:38:37,774 --> 00:38:39,025
...one.

586
00:38:47,450 --> 00:38:49,452
(LOUD EXPLOSION)

587
00:38:55,542 --> 00:39:00,004
Exoglass repair.
Exoglass repair.

588
00:39:04,175 --> 00:39:08,847
Exoglass repair.
Exoglass repair.

589
00:39:08,930 --> 00:39:11,057
(PANTING)

590
00:39:14,018 --> 00:39:15,812
(SIZZLING)

591
00:39:46,593 --> 00:39:48,261
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

592
00:39:52,432 --> 00:39:54,183
(SOBBING)

593
00:39:55,018 --> 00:39:57,061
-ROSE: You all right?
-Yeah, I'm fine.

594
00:39:57,145 --> 00:39:59,564
I'm full of ideas.
I'm bristling with 'em!

595
00:39:59,647 --> 00:40:03,109
Idea number one,
teleportation through 5,000 degrees

596
00:40:03,192 --> 00:40:05,028
needs some kind of feed.

597
00:40:05,111 --> 00:40:08,698
Idea number two.
This feed must be hidden nearby.

598
00:40:12,452 --> 00:40:13,620
Idea number three.

599
00:40:13,703 --> 00:40:18,082
If you're as clever as me,
then a teleportation-feed can be reversed.

600
00:40:18,166 --> 00:40:19,459
(WHINING)

601
00:40:19,542 --> 00:40:24,172
Oh, you should've seen
their little alien faces...

602
00:40:26,382 --> 00:40:28,760
-Oh.
-The last human.

603
00:40:28,843 --> 00:40:31,888
So, you passed
my little test. Bravo!

604
00:40:31,971 --> 00:40:35,141
This makes you eligible
to join the...the Human Club.

605
00:40:35,224 --> 00:40:38,061
People have died Cassandra,
you murdered them.

606
00:40:38,144 --> 00:40:40,313
It depends on your definition
of people!

607
00:40:40,396 --> 00:40:44,275
And that's enough of a technicality to keep
your lawyers dizzy for centuries!

608
00:40:44,359 --> 00:40:49,322
Take me to court then, Doctor,
and watch me smile and cry...

609
00:40:49,405 --> 00:40:50,949
(CREAKING)

610
00:40:51,032 --> 00:40:52,784
-...and flutter.
-And creak?

611
00:40:53,326 --> 00:40:56,037
-And what?
-Creak! You're creaking.

612
00:40:56,996 --> 00:40:59,040
What?

613
00:40:59,123 --> 00:41:01,042
(GRUNTING) I'm drying out!

614
00:41:01,292 --> 00:41:05,046
Oh, sweet heavens!
Moisturise me, moisturise me!

615
00:41:05,129 --> 00:41:08,091
Where are my surgeons?
My lovely boys!

616
00:41:08,174 --> 00:41:11,052
-It's too hot! (GROANING)
-You raised the temperature.

617
00:41:11,219 --> 00:41:13,429
Have pity!

618
00:41:13,513 --> 00:41:15,223
Moisturise me!

619
00:41:15,306 --> 00:41:17,600
(GROANING) Oh, Doctor!

620
00:41:17,684 --> 00:41:19,185
Help her.

621
00:41:19,268 --> 00:41:21,813
Everything has its time
and everything dies.

622
00:41:22,647 --> 00:41:26,943
(SCREAMING)
I'm too young!

623
00:41:39,789 --> 00:41:42,709
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Shuttles four and six departing.

624
00:41:43,126 --> 00:41:46,629
This unit now closing
down for maintenance.

625
00:41:51,926 --> 00:41:53,636
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

626
00:42:02,061 --> 00:42:03,980
The end of the Earth.

627
00:42:05,815 --> 00:42:07,483
It's gone.

628
00:42:10,403 --> 00:42:13,906
We were too busy
saving ourselves. No one saw it go.

629
00:42:18,536 --> 00:42:22,582
All those years,
all that history, and no one was even looking!

630
00:42:24,584 --> 00:42:26,586
It's just...

631
00:42:27,795 --> 00:42:29,130
Come with me.

632
00:42:58,034 --> 00:43:00,119
(CHILD CRYING)

633
00:43:02,580 --> 00:43:04,499
(LAUGHING)

634
00:43:12,381 --> 00:43:14,258
Big Issue!

635
00:43:15,510 --> 00:43:17,512
Big Issue!

636
00:43:17,845 --> 00:43:22,266
You think it'll last forever,
people and cars and concrete.

637
00:43:23,101 --> 00:43:25,103
But it won't.

638
00:43:25,186 --> 00:43:27,230
One day, it's all gone.

639
00:43:28,189 --> 00:43:29,774
Even the sky.

640
00:43:36,697 --> 00:43:38,449
My planet's gone.

641
00:43:39,826 --> 00:43:41,369
It's dead.

642
00:43:43,830 --> 00:43:45,790
It burned, like the Earth.

643
00:43:46,290 --> 00:43:48,417
It's just rocks and dust.

644
00:43:50,002 --> 00:43:51,838
Before its time.

645
00:43:53,756 --> 00:43:55,091
What happened?

646
00:43:57,301 --> 00:44:00,012
There was a war, and we lost.

647
00:44:00,096 --> 00:44:02,014
ROSE: A war with who?

648
00:44:05,685 --> 00:44:07,603
(CLEARS THROAT)
What about your people?

649
00:44:09,147 --> 00:44:11,190
I'm a Time Lord.

650
00:44:11,274 --> 00:44:13,651
I'm the last of
the Time Lords.

651
00:44:14,443 --> 00:44:17,864
They're all gone.
I'm the only survivor.

652
00:44:19,907 --> 00:44:22,160
I'm left traveling on my own
'cause there's no-one else.

653
00:44:23,995 --> 00:44:25,371
There's me.

654
00:44:29,292 --> 00:44:32,170
You've seen
how dangerous it is. Do you wanna go home?

655
00:44:36,382 --> 00:44:37,925
I don't know.

656
00:44:39,552 --> 00:44:41,387
I want...

657
00:44:42,513 --> 00:44:44,098
(SNIFFING)

658
00:44:44,599 --> 00:44:46,893
Oh. Can you smell chips?

659
00:44:47,727 --> 00:44:51,105
-(LAUGHING) Yeah! Yeah.
-I want chips.

660
00:44:51,355 --> 00:44:52,481
Me too!

661
00:44:52,565 --> 00:44:55,818
All right then, before you can get me in that
box, chips it is and you can pay.

662
00:44:56,569 --> 00:44:59,739
-No money.
-What sort of date are you?

663
00:44:59,822 --> 00:45:01,866
Come on then, tightwad.
Chips are on me.

664
00:45:03,409 --> 00:45:05,828
We've only got
five billion years till the shops close.

665
00:45:05,912 --> 00:45:07,580
(CHUCKLES)

666
00:45:16,505 --> 00:45:18,799
Now, you've seen
the future, so let's have a look at the past.

667
00:45:18,883 --> 00:45:21,219
1860. How does 1860 sound?

668
00:45:21,302 --> 00:45:23,721
-What happened in 18607
-I don't know! Let's find out.

669
00:45:25,514 --> 00:45:26,807
REDPATH:
I can't believe she's gone.

670
00:45:26,891 --> 00:45:30,645
Not gone, Mr Redpath, sir.
Merely sleeping.

671
00:45:31,604 --> 00:45:33,773
She's up and on her feet
and out there somewhere!

672
00:45:33,856 --> 00:45:37,360
Mr Sneed, for shame,
how many more times? It's ungodly!

673
00:45:37,443 --> 00:45:38,486
(SHRIEKING)

674
00:45:38,569 --> 00:45:40,613
Excuse me, sir.
Mr Dickens, this is your call.

675
00:45:41,030 --> 00:45:45,618
Use the sight.
Find the old lady or you're dismissed.

676
00:45:46,160 --> 00:45:49,330
What phantasmagoria is this?

677
00:45:49,455 --> 00:45:50,957
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

678
00:45:51,249 --> 00:45:52,583
That's more like it!

